	<div class="first-section">
		<p class="prose">My Chemical Romance’s <i>The Black Parade</i> comes out on top, but Juice Wrld’s <i>Goodbye & Good Riddance</i> and XXXtentacion’s <i>?</i> fall closely behind. For what it’s worth, both emo-rap albums are far ahead of Dashboard, Fall Out Boy, and Jimmy Eat World.
		</p>
		<p class="prose">As expected, artists such as Lil Pump and Migos appear lower on our emo index, which means the data is roughly measuring what it’s supposed to.
		</p>
		<p class="prose">We’ve also charted three of Kanye’s albums, from least to most emo: <i>The College Dropout</i>, <i>808s and the Heartbreaks</i>, and <i>Ye</i> (Kanye’s most emo album according to the data).
		</p>
